I"®<h1 id="how-to-add-a-twitter-account-feed-to-your-event-page">How to add a Twitter account feed to your event page?</h1>

<ol>
  <li>Click on <strong>Event Dashboard</strong> of the event you want to add a Twitter account.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/images/How-to-add-a-Twitter-account-feed-to-your-event-page-1.png" alt="Adding Twitter" /></p>

<ol>
  <li>When you are at the <strong>Overview page</strong>, look for <strong>Links and Social Media</strong> section under the <strong>General Info</strong> column on the right &amp; click to proceed.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/images/How-to-add-a-Twitter-account-feed-to-your-event-page-2.png" alt="Adding Twitter" /></p>

<ol>
  <li>You will be directed to next page where you can modify eventâ€™s <strong>Basic Details</strong>. Scroll down to <strong>Links and Social Media</strong> section.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/images/How-to-add-a-Twitter-account-feed-to-your-event-page-3.png" alt="Adding Twitter" /></p>

<ol>
  <li>Input your Twitter handle with the correct url. When you are done, click <strong>Publish</strong> (at the bottom of the page) to save the details.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/images/How-to-add-a-Twitter-account-feed-to-your-event-page-4.png" alt="Adding Twitterr" /></p>

<ol>
  <li>Now your Twitter feed will appear on the right of your event page as below.</li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/images/How-to-add-a-Twitter-account-feed-to-your-event-page-5.png" alt="Adding Twitter" /></p>
